Dell Technologies Inc DELL | \(\) 134.29\(Outperform | Target Price / Base Case\) \ \(160.00\) Earnings Report
Company StatisticsMarket Capitalization (M)$91,824Shares Outstanding (M)685Float (M)310Average 10-Day Volume (M)3,984Enterprise Value (M)$91,17352-Week Range$66.25 - $147.66Fiscal Year EndJan
1 Year Price History

ALL YOU NEED TO KNOW: DELL reported an impressive Jul- qtr print and materially raised their FY26 guide. July- qtr came in at \(29.8B / 2.32\) vs. street at \(29.0B / 2.29\) - as overall sales were up \(\sim 19\%\) y/y driven by ISG growth of \(44\%\) (Al servers \(+165\%\) , x86 servers up \(4\%\) , storage down \(3\%\) ) and CSG growth of \(\sim 1\%\) . Operating margins came in at \(7.7\%\) - driven by CSG margins growing by \(\sim 120\) bps q/q to \(6.4\%\) , while ISG margins were down 90bps to \(8.8\%\) (storage + Americas impact + Al). For FY26 DELL raised their FY26 guide to \(12\%\) sales growth (prior \(8\%\) ) and noted they expected Al server revenues of \(20B\) (prior \(15B\) ) and EPS of \(9.55\) (prior \(9.40\) ). The key drivers for rev/margin uplift in H2 include - expansion of Al compute margins (less ramp/expedited costs), ISG uptick from storage seasonality and improvement in Americas (x86 servers) and share gains on CSG. We suspect investors will focus on DELL's ability to drive margins up \(\sim 250\) bps in H2 vs. H1 - we think this is more driven by seasonal assumptions + lack of 1x ramp-up costs in H2. Net/Net: Sticking with our OP rating and \(\) 160\(target as we think DELL remains positioned to sustain high single digit sales growth and get to a\) \ \(12+\) EPS quarterly run- rate in FY27.

Jul- qtr Recap: DELL reported Jul- qtr revenue of \(29.8B\) (+19.0% y/y) and non- GAAP EPS of \(2.32\) beating street estimates of \(29.0B / 2.29\) . The topline beat was driven by better- than- expected Al server revenue of \(8.26\) (ahead of the \(\sim 7B\) guide). Notably, Al orders were \(5.6B\) (vs. \(\) 12.1\(B L Q)\) , while backlog declined to\)\\(11.7B\) (vs. \(\) 14.4B\(L Q)\) . From a segment standpoint, Client Solutions revenue of \(12.5B\) was up \(0.7\%\) y/y (commercial up \(2.1\%\) , consumer down \(- 7.3\%\) ) while Infrastructure Solutions Group revenue of \(16.8B\) grew by \(44.3\%\) y/y (Servers & Networking up \(68.7\%\) , but Storage was down \(- 3.0\%\) y/y). Gross margin during the quarter came in at \(18.7\%\) and operating margin was \(7.7\%\) . Client Solutions operating margin in the quarter was \(6.4\%\) (vs. \(5.2\%\) LQ), while Infrastructure Solutions segment margin \(8.8\%\) (vs. \(9.7\%\) LQ). DELL generated \(\) 2,506M\(in cash flow from operations and free- cash flow of\) \ \(1,868M\) (adjusting for DFS, FCF was \(\) 2,518M\(in the Jul- qtr).

Oct- qtr & FY26 Outlook: For the Oct- qtr, management indicated that revenue will be up \(11\%\) y/y at the midpoint ( \(26.5 - 27.5B\) ), vs. street at \(27.1B\) . DELL expects EPS of \(\) 2.45\((+ / - 10c)\) , below street at \(\) 2.55\(CSG is expected to grow mid- single digits, while ISG is expected to grow in the low - 20\%\) range. ISG and CSG is expected to be up a combined \(+13\%\) y/y at midpoint. Opex is expected to continue to decline low single digits y/y in FQ3. For FY26, DELL raised its rev guide to \(\) 105 - 109B\((+12\%\) y/y at midpoint), up from its prior guide of\) \ \(101 - 105B\) . The FY26 guide reflects ISG growth of mid- to- high \(20\%\) , which includes flat y/y storage sales, while CSG is expected to grow low- to- mid single digits. In addition, DELL raised its FY26 Al server revenue target to \(\) 20B+\(from\) \ \(15B+\) . Together, the combined segments are expected to grow \(+14\%\) at midpoint. Opex for the year is expected to be down low single digits, while operating profit is expected to be up \(\sim 10\%\) y/y. For EPS, DELL raised its guide to \(\) 9.55\((+ / - 25c)\) , up from its prior guide of \(\) 9.40\$ .

Balance Sheet & Cash Flow: During the Jul- qtr, DELL generated cash flow from operations of \(2,543M and free- cash flow of\) 1,868M (adjusting for DFS, FCF was \(2.518B in the Jul- qtr). DELL ended the quarter with a total cash balance of\) 8.1B. Total debt balance ended up at \(28.9B (total core debt ex- DFC debt ended at\) 16.3B).

DELL reportedull-qtr revenue of $29.8B (+19.0% y/y) and non-GAAP EPS of $2.32 beating street estimates of $29.0B/$2.29. The topline beat was driven by better-than-expected Al server revenue of $8.2B (ahead of the $-$7B guide). Notably, Al orders were $5.6B (vs. $12.1B LQ),while log declined to $11.7B (vs. $14.4B LQ). From a segment standpoint, Client Solutions revenue of $12.5B was up 0.7% y/y (commercial up 2.1%, consumer down -7.3%) while Infrastructure Solutions Group revenue of $16.8B grew by 44.3% y/y (Servers & Networking up 68.7%;but Storage was down -3.0% y/y). Gross margin during the quarter came in at 18.7% and operating margin was 7.7%. Client Solutions operating margin in the quarter was 6.4% (vs. 5.2% LQ), while Infrastructure Solutions segment margin 8.8% (vs. 9.7% LQ). DELL generated $2,506M in cash flow from operations and free-cash flow of $1,868M (adjusting for DFS, FCF was $2.518B in the Jul-qtr).

For the Oct-qtr, management indicated that revenue will be up 11% y/y at the midpoint ($26.5-27.5B), vs. street at $27.1B. DELL expects EPS of $2.45 (+/- 10c), below street at $2.55. CSG is expected to grow mid-single digits, while ISG is expected to grow in the low-20% range. ISG and CSG is expected to be up a combined +13% y/y at midpoint. Opex is expected to continue to decline low single digits y/y in FQ3. For FY26, DELL raised its rev guide to $105-109B (+12% y/y at midpoint), up from its prior guide of $101-105B. The FY26 guide reflects ISG growth of mid-to-high 20%, which includes flat y/y storage sales, while CSG is expected to grow low-to-mid single digits. In addition, DELL raised its FY26 AI server revenue target to $20B (from $15B+). Together, the combined segments are expected to grow +14% at midpoint. Management also noted that it expects improved profitability in H2, driven in part by margins in CSG and storage, along with improved traditional server mix. Opex for the year is expected to be down low single digits, while operating profit is expected to be up ~10% y/y. For EPS, DELL raised its guide to $9.55 (+/- 25c), up from its prior guide of $9.40.

Client Solutions (42% of Revenue): DELL's Client Solutions segment revenue of \(12.5B was up 0.7\% y/y. Consumer was down y/y (- 7.3\% y/y) while Commercial was up y/y (+2.1\% y/y). Client Solutions operating margin was down -20bps y/y at 6.4\% and operating income was\) 803M.

VALUATION METHODOLOGYOur Target Price is based on a price/earnings multiple. We assess future earnings growth, operating margins, free cash flow generation and returns on capital employed when determining whether a company is deserving of higher or lower multiples.

RISKS1) Potential slowdown in broader global IT spend; 2) High debt balance could limit financial flexibility and also impact Dell's ability to provide future shareholder returns; 3) Competition from emerging vendors; and 4) Corporate governance.

Evercore ISI's recommendations are based on a stock's total forecasted return over the next 12 months. Total forecasted return is equal to the expected percentage price return plus gross dividend yield. We divide our stocks under coverage into three primary ratings categories, with the following return guidelines:

Outperform- the total forecasted return is expected to be greater than the expected total return of the analyst's coverage sector. In Line- the total forecasted return is expected to be in line with the expected total return of the analyst's coverage sector. Underperform- the total forecasted return is expected to be less than the expected total return of the analyst's coverage sector. Coverage Suspended- the rating and target price have been removed pursuant to Evercore ISI policy when Evercore is acting in an advisory capacity in a merger or strategic transaction involving this company and in certain other circumstances. Rating Suspended- Evercore ISI has suspended the rating and target price for this stock because there is not sufficient fundamental basis for determining, or there are legal, regulatory or policy constraints around publishing, a rating or target price. The previous rating and target price, if any, are no longer in effect for this company and should not be relied upon.
Prior to October 10, 2015, the "Coverage Suspended" and "Rating Suspended" categories were included in the category "Suspended."
